{"word":"αἰδοῖος","slug":"αἰδοῖος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αἰδοῖος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:αἰδέομαι'><el>αἰδέομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b>of persons, <i>regarded with reverence, august, venerable</i>, and of women, <i>deserving respect, tender</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>shamefaced, reverent</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ως</el>, <i>reverently</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>αἰδοιότερος</el>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>αἰδοιέστατος</el>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}